    <h1>Novum Organum</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Francis Bacon · 1620 · <a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/45988">Full text (Project Gutenberg)</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Stop deducing from axioms. Start collecting observations. Arrange them in tables. Let the pattern declare itself. Bacon replaced Aristotelian syllogism with <strong>systematic induction</strong>, and insisted that the observer's job is to report what is there, not what ought to be.</p>
    </div>

